bill.title: Certificate of public need; definition of ""medical care facility.""
bill.abstract: Certificate of public need; definition of ""medical care facility."" Adds to the list of medical care facilities for which a certificate of public need is required any facility that has common ownership with an affiliated licensed hospital located within 35 miles of the facility and that includes, as part of the facility, a dedicated emergency department as defined in 42 C.F.R. 489.24(b) that is subject to the requirements of the federal Emergency Medical Treatment and Labor Act.
